The paper deals with characterizing the degrees of freedom of a communication channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). Specifically, it focuses on interference channels, which are a subfield of network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of multilevel coding, which is a technique used in source coding (cs.SI) and channel coding (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of nested lattice structures, which are commonly used in signal processing (cs.MM) and coding theory (cs.CC).
